Commentary: A length ball, way outside off, hint of shape there. Elgar leaves it alone.
A length ball, from around the wicket and around off. Elgar blocks it.
Short of a length and way outside off. Elgar lets it through to the keeper.
Angles a full ball, around middle. Elgar leans and blocks it to covers.
Touch fuller and around off. Elgar prods and drops it wide of covers for a single. South Africa are underway.
Back of a length and around off, this one just holds it line but Sarel Erwee gets a straight bat down to keep it out.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Left alone.
Flatter and angling on middle, skids through the surface. Elgar hangs on the back foot and flicks it wide of mid-wicket for three runs.
Fuller and on off. Erwee prods and blocks it.
FOUR! First boundary and a good one! This is short and outside off. Erwee cuts it hard and past point for a boundary.
Too full and slanting on off. Erwee leans and defends it out.
Full again, tailing on middle. Erwee defends on the front foot.
Short in length and on off. Elgar drops it in front of covers and takes a quick single.
Good length ball, around off. Erwee keeps his bat near the body and defends it on the off side.
On a length and around off, pushed to mid on.

A huge shout for LBW but nothing given! Ahmed thinks of taking the review but Mominul Haque wasn't much convinced and they opt not to take it. A length ball, this one angles around off and nips back in as well. Erwee lunges to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Would have been very tight. Oh, dear! The replay showed that it would have been out! Ball Tracking indicates three reds! Other than the bowler, nobody else was convinced to go for the review!
Length and on off. Erwee defends it out.
Short and around off, jags back in but Erwee shoulders arms to it.
Starts with a length ball from 'round the wicket and outside off. Elgar offers no shot.
A yorker, angling around off. Elgar jams it out to covers and scampers across for a quick  single.
Length ball, outside off. Erwee shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, around off. Erwee looks to defend but gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
Inside edge again but this time the length was on the shorter side and the ball rolls to the on side.
Short of a length, outside off, this is hit to point.
On a length, darting it around the hips. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
On a length and outside off. Defended out.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Touch fuller and outside off. Elgar leans and punches it gently through covers for a boundary. Good shot this.
A length ball, outside off, a late in dipper. Elgar shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, this is nudged to square leg.
A length ball, around off. Elgar guides it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Length ball, way outside off. Erwee is happy to leave it alone.
This one keeps on coming with the angle, on the pads, it is flicked to fine leg for a single.
Outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, around off, keeps a bit low. Elgar awkwardly pushes it to mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, Erwee works it to mid-wicket for a run.
A length ball, drifting on middle. Elgar blocks it on the deck.
Length ball, on middle. Erwee pushes it nicely straight down but Ahmed does well to stop it.
Fuller and angling around off. Erwee dead bats it.
Fuller, straight and over the wicket, flicked to square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller and around off. Erwee pushes it to mid off.
Too full and on middle. Erwee pushes it right off the middle of the blade but straight to mid on.
Angles a length ball, across. Erwee leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, it is hit to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Punched away! Short of a length, around off. Elgar gets into the position quickly and punches off the back foot through the vacant cover region for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Elgar works it to point.
A length ball, angling outside off and straightening off the deck. Elgar half-heartedly prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, pushed through covers for a couple.
Tossed up, full and bit of turn there. Erwee keeps it out.
FOUR! Fuller and angling on middle. Erwee gets low and paddles it to fine leg. Fast outfield here and the ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Tossed up, slower in the air and on middle. Erwee hits through the line and back to the bowler.
Short and way outside off, cut away to point where the fielder dives to his left to stop it.
Very full and on middle. Erwee whips it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! South Africa are not letting Hasan settle here. Shorter and outside off. Elgar punches off the back foot through the gap in covers for a boundary.
Angles a length ball, on the pads. Erwee misses his flick and gets hit high on the pads. An appeal for LBW but that was angling way down.
FOUR! Boundaries coming nicely for the Proteas! This is full and outside off. Erwee looks to drive but gets a thickish outside edge and through gully region for another boundary.
Way down the leg side. Erwee shuffles across and looks to flick it but it went of the thigh pads to the keeper.
Length and way outside off. Erwee leaves it after covering his stumps.
On a length and around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Yet another boundary! A length ball, too straight and on the pads. Erwee whacks it to long leg for a boundary.
Fuller ball, tosses it up, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar leans to block this but he gets an inside edge away from the short leg fielder.
Quicker, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shorter ball, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and slashes it past point for a boundary. 50 up for South Africa!
Spinning away, outside off, touch short again. Dean Elgar pushes it towards past point for a single.
Flatter ball this time, much straighter, around middle. Sarel Erwee punches it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery, full, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
On a length, outside off, shaping away, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Another length delivery, outside off, aro 135 kph. Sarel Erwee lets that go through to the keeper.
On a length, around middle and off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee offer no shot.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bangladesh finally have their first breakthrough. Khaled Ahmed strikes and draws first blood. A fuller ball, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leans and looks to drive this away from his body, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards the keeper. Liton Das dives to his left and takes a good catch. Sarel Erwee departs!
Howout: c Liton Das b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar presses forward and blocks it out.
Tosses it up again, full, around off. Dean Elgar defends it out.
Firing it on the stumps, fuller ball. Dean Elgar defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, turning away, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards sweeper cover for a single.
Fuller delivery around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
Pitches it up, outside off. Dean Elgar opens the face of the bat and drives it towards the fielder at point.
FOUR! Pulled away! Khaled Ahmed drops it short now, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and smashes it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar punches it off the back foot towards cover for a single.
Outside off, on a length. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Marginally short, outside off. Keegan Petersen punches it past cover for a brace.
Beaten! Lovely delivery! Outside off, tad shorter, shaping away. Keegan Petersen looks to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards cover.
Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar leans and taps it away from the fielder at short leg.
Outside off this time, fuller ball. Dean Elgar blocks it out solidly.
Around the pads, fuller ball. Dean Elgar tucks it towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Oh! That was a tight leave from Dean Elgar! Tosses it up, full, outside off. Dean Elgar prods and leaves it alone. The ball goes just past the off pole.
Shorter ball, outside off. Dean Elgar defends it out from within the crease.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar taps it towards point.
Fuller ball, angling in, around middle. Dean Elgar closes the face of his bat and taps it towards square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off, at 137 clicks. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Keegan Petersen flicks it past square leg. Two taken!
Pitches it up, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen shows the full face of his bat and pushes it back to the bowler.
Swinging in, outside off, shorter ball. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards point.
Loopy delivery, full, on the pads. Dean Elgar knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Spinning away, full, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and blocks it out.
FOUR! Perfectly timed! A fuller ball, down leg. Dean Elgar uses his wrists, closes the face of his bat, and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tad shorter now, around middle. Dean Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Dean Elgar defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar works it away towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Yorker-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen digs it out.
Very full again, width on offer this time. Keegan Petersen leans, gets down on his knee, and drives it towards the fielder at cover.
Pitches it up, outside off. Keegan Petersen once again drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Angling in, on a length, outside off, at 137 clicks. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen punches it off the back foot past cover for a brace.
Taijul Islam begins with a flatter ball, full, around off. Dean Elgar pushes it to the left of the bowler, Taijul Islam dives to his left and stops the ball.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Firing it on the pads, fuller ball. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg.
Much straighter, full, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker now, full again, around middle. Keegan Petersen defends it out.
Shortish delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen defends it out off the back foot.

FOUR! Fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar flicks it past mid on. Tamim Iqbal chases the ball, dives, and keeps the ball away from the ropes, but he has made a connection with the boundary ropes in the process. Boundary!
Outside off, on a length. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the back foot.
1 run. Tad shorter, outside off. Dean Elgar dabs it towards point and takes a single.
Back of a length, outside off, at 134 clicks. Keegan Petersen taps it toward gully.
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen lunges and blocks it out.
Full and on middle, eased to long on for a single.
On middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and on off. Petersen punches it to covers.
Nice shot but for no run! This is full and angling on middle. Petersen drives it but straight to covers.
Around off, full and blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
A length ball, outside off, this one nips back in. Elgar looks to drive on the up but misses.
A short ball, targeted on middle. Elgar looks to pulls without much conviction and misses. A stifled appeal follows for a caught behind but nothing happening.
Length and on off. Kept out.
Around off, on a length. Elgar guides it to point for a single. That also brings up fifty for the skipper, Dean Elgar, playing at a very good rate and making sure his team gets off to a good start.
Length and on middle, Petersen pushes it through covers for a single.
A length ball, just outside off. Elgar works it to covers.
Too full and on off, pushed to covers.
Full again, angling on middle, pushed back to Islam.
Flatter and on middle. Petersen hangs back and hits it on the leg side.
Slower through the air, on a length and on middle. Petersen defends on the front foot.
On the pads, flicked to square leg.
A quicker one, slanting around off. Petersen punches it through covers for a couple of runs.
A length ball, on middle. Elgar pushes it to mid on.
Same length and line as the previous delivery. This time Elgar defends it with his bat and pad together.
A length ball, angling outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, swinging on middle, tucked to square leg.
FOUR! Welcome boundary! Short of a length and around off. Elgar pulls it well wide of mid-wicket and bags a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Elgar is playing beautifully here! Short again and wide outside off. Elgar opens the face of the bat, uses the pace just to guide it through gully for a boundary.
FOUR! This is short and angling on off, turning away. Petersen rocks back and cuts it past first slip and to third man for a boundary.
A floated ball, on middle. Petersen leans and blocks it.
Fuller and angling down. Petersen prods and pushes it to mid on.
Too full and on off. Petersen keeps it out.
Tossed up, angling around off. Petersen blocks it solidly on the front foot.
A flighted ball, almost a yorker. Petersen squeezes it out to third man for a single.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! A shorter ball, around middle. Keegan Petersen pulls it towards square leg. Mehidy Hasan fails to stop the ball due to some extra bounce. The ball rolls towards the fence for a boundary. 100 up for South Africa!
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely done! On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen hangs back, opens the face of the bat, and guides it past point for a boundary. That brings up the 50-run partnership between these two!
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end.
Well bowled! On a length, outside off, and shaping away a tad. Dean Elgar looks to block this, but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angling in, around middle, on a length. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen defends it out.
Marginally short now, around middle. Keegan Petersen rocks back, makes room, and cuts it towards point. ,
Fuller delivery, flatter as well, on middle. Keegan Petersen defends it out watchfully.
Tosses it up now, full, around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it towards cover.
Slower through the air, full, around off. Keegan Petersen pushes it toward mid off.
Tad quicker now, around middle and off, fuller ball, at around 90 kph. Keegan Petersen defends it out.
Shortish ball, around off. Dean Elgar pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Fuller ball, down the leg side. Dean Elgar tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller ball, slower through the air, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it past mid off for a single.
Shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the back foot.
Tosses it up, full, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and defends it out.
Another full delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and taps it towards point. Keegan Petersen wanted a single there, but Dean Elgar says no! That will be Lunch on Day 1!
Fuller delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and blocks it out.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen presses forward and defends it out.

Slower through the air, fuller in length,around off. Keegan Petersen advances down the pitch and looks to push this away, but the ball goes off the outside edge away from first slip towards third man. Two taken!
Shortish delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out off the back foot.
FOUR! First boundary of the session! Loopy delivery, full again, around off. Keegan Petersen dances down the pitch and drives it past cover for a boundary.
Pitches it up, around middle. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards mid off.
On a length, outside off. Dean Elgar taps it towards point and takes a quick single
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and defends it out.
Outside off, tad shorter again. Keegan Petersen dabs it towards point.
FOUR! Crunched! Ebadot Hossain drops it short this time, around middle. Keegan Petersen picks up the length, swivels, and pulls it past mid-wicket for a cracking boundary.
Angling in, around the thigh pads. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards fine leg for a single. He retains the strike.
Fuller and on off, pushed past the bowler to mid off for a single.
Length ball, flighted and turning around middle. Elgar ticks it to square leg.
Length and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Blocked out.
Full again, on middle. Petersen defends on the front foot.
Another solid front foot defense from Petersen.
FOUR! Superb shot! A length ball, around off. Elgar presses on the front foot and punches it in the gap, to covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Aggressive stuff from the skipper! Short this time with width allowed. Elgar cuts it through gully for a boundary.
Length ball, around off, jags back in. Dean bunts it to mid-wicket for a single.
Very full and around off. Petersen jams it back to Hossain.
Length ball at 135 kph, angling around off. Petersen plays with soft hands to mid-wicket for a single.
Wide! Changes the angle and comes 'round the wicket with a short ball. Elgar leaves it. A wide given for height.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Angles a length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Kept out.
Slightly full and on  off, driven through point for a single.
A huge shout for LBW but given! Sharp turn there! FLatter and landing around middle, it turns onto the pads sharply. Elgar misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bangladesh get the big wicket of Dean Elgar! The previous delivery had a sharp turn but not so much in this one as it comes straight off the deck, on a length, and outside off. Dean Elgar shuffles a bit and looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and Liton Das, the keeper takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Bavuma defends it to silly point.

A big shout for LBW and the umpire is unmoved. This is on a length and slanting around off, it nips back in sharply. Petersen looks to flick it but misses and gets hit high on the pads. Yes, the replay shows it was going onto miss the stumps.
On the pads, Petersen flicks it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Fuller ball, around off. Petersen leans into his drive and hits it wide of covers and left of mid off for a boundary. He moves to 44 now.

FOUR! Edged away! Short of a length and outside off, extra bounce there! Petersen looks to push with hard hands but gets an outside edge past the gully fielder for a boundary. Was well away from the fielder there.

FOUR! Fifty for Keegan Petersen! Hat-trick of boundaries for him to reach the milestone. Once Elgar departed, he has changed the gears here hitting away the loose deliveries! Overptched and outside off, driven through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Bavuma pushes it through covers for a couple of runs.
Angles a length ball, on middle. Defended out.
A slider, around leg. Bavuma goes back and keeps it out.
Shorter and outside off. Bavuma taps it down to backward point.
Full and outside off. Bavuma prods and dead bats it.
Full again, around off. Bavuma blocks it out.
Full ball, on off. Petersen gets a straight bat down to defend it.
Full and on the pads. Petersen flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
On a length and on off. Blocked out.
Tad short and angling on middle. Petersen pushes it uppishly and just wide of the fielder a mid-wicket.
Full and targeting the stumps. Petersen is solid in his defense.
A length ball, on middle. Kept out.
A loopy ball, outside off. Bavuma hits it to point.
Tossed up, on middle. Bavuma blocks it on the front foot.
Tad short and Bavuma latches on it, cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
FOUR! Short again and more width this time. Bavuma cuts it hard and through cover-point. The fielder gives a chase and almost flicks it back but ends up conceding a boundary.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Tucked wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Almost chopped on! A length ball, around off. Bavuma defends it late and under his eyes but bottom edges it and the ball rolls wide of leg stump.
Length and on middle, it is hit to mid-wicket.
Full ball, on middle, pushed straight back past the bowler but the mid off fielder cuts it off.
On middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, on middle, Petersen works it to mid on but for no run.
Just a single of the over then! Length ball,on off. Petersen hops and wrists it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Bavuma leans and blocks it.
Angles it onto the pads, flicked to square leg for a single.
Too full and on off. Petersen blocks it back on the surface.
A flighted, slow ball, on, middle. Petersen skips down and looks to flick it but gets an inside edge to short fine leg.
Flatter and on off. Kept out.
Shorter and quicker and on off. Petersen looks to punch it but gets a bottom edge and the ball deflects onto his boots. Almost a wicket there for Bangladesh.
Full ball, on off. Bavuma pushes it to mid-wicket.
A yorker, on middle. Bavuma flicks it but again cannot get it past mid-wicket.
On the pads, it is flicked to square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Petersen stays back and punches it to covers.
Length and on off. Blocked back to Ahmed.
Length ball, way down the leg side. Petersen misses his flick.
Shorter ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma cuts it towards point.
Another shortish delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma makes room and pushes it towards cover-point.
Floated and on off. Defended out.
Darted on the pads. Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on off. Bavuma leans and blocks it out.
This is outside off and Bavuma knocks it to point.
Fuller ball, angling in around the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma stays in his crease and pushes it towards cover.
Marginally short, around middle, at 134 clicks. Temba Bavuma hangs back and blocks it out.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length, at 132 clicks. Temba Bavuma taps it towards mid-wicket.
Much straighter this time, length delivery, around off, at 137 kph. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
Khaled Ahmed drops it short this time, around middle. Temba Bavuma ducks underneath it.
Flatter delivery, full, around middle. Keegan Petersen presses forward and defends it out.
Fuller again, around middle. Keegan Petersen steps down the pitch and looks to block this but the ball goes off the inside edge towards square leg for a brace.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and defends it out watchfully.
Shorter ball now, around middle. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards mid on.
Back of a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Pitches it up now, around middle. Keegan Petersen advances down the track and pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller length delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma leans and blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it out solidly off the front foot.
Angling in around middle and leg, fuller in length, at 136 clicks. Temba Bavuma works it away towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover of the back foot.
Shorter ball again, outside off. Temba Bavuma opens the face of the bat and dabs it towards cover-point. A maiden over from Khaled Ahmed!
Fuller ball, tad quicker, at around 89 clicks, around middle. Keegan Petersen defends it out.
Pitches it up again, around off. Keegan Petersen dances down the track and drives it towards cover.
Tosses it up, full in length, on middle. Keegan Petersen presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Shorter ball now, flatter, around middle. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg.
Fuller delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out off the front foot.
Flatter, straighter and shorter. Keegan Petersen taps it towards square leg. Another maiden over for Bangladesh!
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma taps it towards cover-point off the back foot.
On a length now, angling in around the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
Marginally short, outside off. Keegan Petersen punches it towards cover. Taijul Islam there dives to his left and half-stops the ball. Only a single taken!
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Tad short now, outside off. Temba Bavuma gets on top of the bounce, and punches it through cover for a boundary.
Length delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma does not fiddle with it.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Loopy ball once again, very full, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen knocks it towards the fielder at mid on.
Fullish in length, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen presses forward and blocks it out solidly.
Quicker through the air, at 87 clicks, full, around off. Keegan Petersen leans to block this, but the ball goes off the outside edge past silly point for a single.
Shorter in length this time, spinning away, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out off the back foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes past backward point for a single.
Ebadot Hossain drops it short again, down leg. Keegan Petersen ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it towards cover.
Angling in on a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen blocks it out off the back foot.
Back of a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen swivels and pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Very full on this occasion, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Keegan Petersen blocks it out off the back foot.
Fuller delivery now, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen presses forward and defends it out solidly.
Quicker this time, fuller again, around middle. Keegan Petersen keeps it out.
Pitches it up now, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen steps down the pitch and works it away towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery, around middle and leg, fuller in length. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Shortish delivery, darting it on the pads. Keegan Petersen tucks it past short fine leg fielder for a brace.
On a length, angling in, outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Very full on this occasion, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma punches it off the back foot towards sweeper cover for a brace.
On a length, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma leans and defends it out.
Angling in on the pads, fullish length. Temba Bavuma flicks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
FOUR! Easy pickings! shorter delivery, down the leg side. Keegan Petersen swivels and pulls it towards fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Good placement! Fuller ball, outside off, slower this time. Temba Bavuma drives it past the diving fielder at mid off for a boundary. That brings up the 50-run partnership between these two!
Shorter ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it past point for a single.

OUT! LBW! Taijul Islam has been rewarded once again! He gets rid of Keegan Petersen and South Africa lose their third wicket. A fuller delivery, this one comes in with the angle, on the pads. Keegan Petersen advances down the track and tries to flick this but he misses and gets rapped on the pads. A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no. Bangladesh opts for a review! UltraEdge shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows three reds! A successful review for Bangladesh and Keegan Petersen walks back in disbelief.
Howout: lbw b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Flatter ball, quicker, around middle. Ryan Rickelton defends it out.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out off the back foot.
Tosses this one up, full, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton tucks it past short leg.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Temba Bavuma flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Ebadot Hossain drops it short now, outside off. Ryan Rickelton ducks under it.
On a length, around middle. Ryan Rickelton leaves it alone.
Shorter ball, outside off, at around 141 clicks. Ryan Rickelton watches it sail through to the keeper.
Very full now, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it towards cover-point.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Ryan Rickelton defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full and sliding on the pads,flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and around off. Rickelton stays back and keeps it out.
Slightly full and on off. Rickelton pushes it to mid-wicket.
Around off, fuller. Blocked out.
Angling on the pads, Rickelton tickles it to square leg.
A loopy ball, on middle. Bavuma works it to square leg.
Fuller and on middle, Bavuma pushes it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle, Bavnuma pushes it to mid on and calls for a quick single. There is a shy at the bowler's end but misses. A direct-hit would've been very close.
Short and angling outside off. Rickelton covers his stumps and lets it through.
An arm ball, fuller and outside off. Rickelton again makes a good leave.
On middle. Blocked out.
A short ball, outside off. Bavuma cuts it hard and to deep cover. The fielder from deep point runs across and shows his football skills to keep it away from the ropes. Two runs taken.
Angles it on the pads, flicked to square leg for a single.
This one stays a touch low, fuller and on off. Rickelton blocks it out.
FOUR! Off the mark! A loopy ball, on off. Rickelton comes down the track and heaves it, does not get enough distance but hits it in the vacant mid-wicket region and the ball races away to the fence.
Flatter and on middle. Rickelton keeps it out.
This is touch short and around off. Rickelton hangs back and punches it through covers and takes three runs with ease.
Angles a full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Touch quicker and on middle. Rickelton hangs back and guides it to point.
This one spins away, outside off. Rickelton leaves it alone.
Goes wide of the crease and angles a length ball, just outside off. Rickelton covers his stumps and lets it through.
Full and on middle, given more air this time and Rickelton pushes it to cover.
Around off, fuller and Rickelton has his straight bat down to keep it out.
Floated, full and on off. Bavuma dead bats it.
An arm ball, flighted and outside off.Bavuma looks to drive but mistimes it to the bowler.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Straight and on middle, pushed to Islam.
Width there, outside off and Temba hits it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Rickelton blocks it out solidly.
A loopy ball, on off. Bavuma prods and defends it.
Tad short and on middle. Bavuma pulls it, not off the middle and to mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Very full and on middle. Bavuma leans and defends it out.
Floated this time, on middle. Bavuma defends this time to the leg side.
A single to end the over! Full again, on middle. Bavuma works it to deep mid-wicket for a single. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Flatter and on off. Bavuma pushes it to point.
Tossed up, on off. Bavuma on the front foot, defends it out.
Angles this one, full and on middle. Bavuma works it to mid off.
A length ball, around off, hint of away turn. Bavuma defends it towards point.
Bavuma prods and defends this full ball to covers.
200 up for South Africa! Slightly full and outside off. Bavuma hits it through covers for a single.
Full, floated and on off. Bavuma leans and defends it back to Hasan.
Hasan continues to bowl in the same area, full and on off. Bavuma continues to block it out.
Full again but around middle. Temba tucks it to mid-wicket.
Darted onn the pads. Bavuma whips it to deep square leg for a single.
Short and around off, turning away. Rickelton slaps it to point.
Flatter this time, outside off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it towards cover.
Tosses it up, full again, around off. Temba Bavuma leans and defends it out.
Spinning away, outside off, tad shorter. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma taps it towards cover.
Fuller now, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma lunges and blocks it out.
Touch fuller again, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover.
A fuller ball from 'round the wicket, around middle. Ryan Rickelton lunges forward and defends it out.
Shortish delivery, spinning away, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it through cover off the back foot. Two taken!

NOT OUT! A huge shout for LBW but the umpire says no! A shorter ball, spinning away, around middle. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and blocks this. But Bangladesh think it has got the pad first and they opt for a review. UltraEdge shows that the ball has come out of the bat only. Bangladesh lose their review and the original decision stands!
Fuller delivery, around middle. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Ryan Rickelton leans and defends it out.
Loopy delivery, around middle. Ryan Rickelton lunges forward and blocks it out.
Fuller length, around middle and leg. Temba Bavuma leans and defends it out.
Tosses it up now, full, around off. Temba Bavuma presses forward and blocks it out.
Flighted delivery, full, around off. Temba Bavuma lunges and defends it out.
Shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it off the back foot towards cover.
Fuller ball, outside off, loopy delivery. Temba Bavuma leans and taps it towards point and scampers through to the other end.
Fuller delivery, quicker, around middle. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.

Fuller delivery, around off. Temba Bavuma steps down and pushes it to the right of the bowler. He leaves his crease for a run, but Mehidy Hasan dives to his right and stops the ball. Temba Bavuma goes back quickly inside his crease.
Fuller, slower though the air, around middle. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Full again, around middle. Temba Bavuma flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover.
Fuller, quicker, on the pads. Temba Bavuma clips it towards square leg for a brace.
Fuller delivery, around middle. Temba Bavuma leans and blocks it towards square leg.
Shortish delivery, around middle. Ryan Rickelton defends it out off the back foot.
SIX! BANG! Good use of the feet by Ryan Rickelton! A fuller ball, around middle. Ryan Rickelton dances down the track and heaves it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Fuller ball, around middle. Ryan Rickelton knocks it down to long on for a single.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma leans and blocks it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller delivery, drifting it in on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it past the diving fielder at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma steers it past point for a single.
Shorter and spinning back in. Bavuma whips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Very full and on leg. Rickelton leans and tucks it to square leg for one more.
Nice straight, around off. Bavuma pushes it to mid-wicket.
Slower one, on off, it is hit to square leg.
Tossed up, on off. Temba blocks it on the back foot.
Flatter and on middle. Bavuma gets back and tickles it to square leg.
Starts from around the wicket and angles it on middle. Rickelton covers the line and blocks it out.
Full ball, way outside off. Rickelton drives it to deep cover and the sweeper runs across and cuts it out. Two runs taken.
Carbon copy of the previous delivery and the sweeper is again in action. Two runs taken.
On a length and on middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off and coming back in late. Rickelton leaves it alone.
Short of a length, outside off, pulled away to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, pushed to mid off for a single.
Floated, full and on middle. Blocked out.
On middle. Blocked out.
Flighted and on off. Bavuma pushes it to mid off for a single.
Shorter and around the off stump. Rickelton tries to punch but the ball is too near him and ends up hitting it to covers.
Floated and on off. Defended out.
Short in length and on off. Bavuma mistimes his punch to mid-wicket.
On the hips, flicked behind square on the leg side for a single. Bavuma thinks for another run but does not take the risk.
Angles it on the pads, flicked to 45 for a single.
On a length and on off. Bavuma gets inside the line and hops to defend it out.
Length and on off. Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket and hurls across for a quick single. Rickelton had to hurry but makes it nicely.
Length ball, outside off. Ryan punches it to deep point and easily takes a couple of runs.
Fuller and on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fifty for Temba Bavuma! 19th Test fifty for him, consistency from Bavuma! Shorter and on middle. He pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Short again and on middle. Bavuma pounces on it as he pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Gives more flight to this one, on middle. Bavuma is happy to defend.
Another solid defensive stroke from Bavuma to end the over.
Shortish ball, darting it on the pads. Ryan Rickelton nudges it towards square leg for a single.
Short again, spinning away, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover for a single.
Turning in, around middle, fuller ball. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.
Quicker, fuller, around middle. Ryan Rickelton defends it out of the back foot.
Loopy delivery, full, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it towards cover.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton taps it towards square leg for a single.
Shortish delivery, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller delivery, around middle. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller in length, around middle and leg. Temba Bavuma clips it towards mid-wicket.
Shortish ball, spinning in, around middle. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, around middle, spinning in. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller now, loopy delivery, around middle. Ryan Rickelton defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, spinning away, around off. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
Shortish delivery now, around middle. Temba Bavuma defends it out off the back foot now.
Fuller ball, around middle. Temba Bavuma leans and blocks it out.
Shortish ball, around middle. Temba Bavuma pushes it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up, full, outside off. Temba Bavuma taps it towards cover.
Fuller ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma taps it towards point.
Loopy ball, full, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Ryan Rickelton presses forward and defends it out.
Flighted delivery, outside off, full in length. Ryan Rickelton pushes it back to the bowler.
Full again, outside off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out watchfully.
Tosses it up, full, spinning away, around off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.
Another loopy delivery, pitches it up, outside off. Ryan Rickelton defends it out.
Shorter ball, spinning in, around middle. Temba Bavuma pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Fuller delivery, turning in, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Tosses it up, full, outside off. Temba Bavuma presses forward and defends it out.
Shortish delivery, turning in, around middle. Temba Bavuma flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, around middle and off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Outside off, shorter ball. Temba Bavuma cuts it towards sweeper for a single. He retains the strike.
Tossed up, sliding on middle. Bavuma pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller and around off. Bavuma gets low and paddles it to fine leg and there is no one present to chase this one. A boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Temba keeps it out.
Too full and targeting the stumps. Bavuma dead bats it.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
A floated, full ball, on off. Defended out by Temba.
Loopy ball, on middle.  Rickelton gets an inside edge as he looks to defend it. The ball rolls to short fine leg.
Flighted and turning away, outside off. Rickelton pads it away.
Floated and outside off. Defended out.
Tad short and outside off. Ryan works it to point.
FOUR! Positive shot! Fuller and on off. Rickelton reverse sweeps it wide of short third man for a boundary.
Slants it on a length and on middle. Rickelton rocks back and keeps it out on the leg side.

A huge, huge appeal for a caught behind but nothing given! A flatter ball, on a length angling around off and spinning away. Bavuma prods to defend towards cover but seems to miss it. The keeper collects and appeals for it. They do not take the review. The replay shows the noise was off the bat brushing the pad.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Length ball, on middle. Bavuma drills it out to mid off.
Slides a length ball, around leg. Bavuma lunges to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but that was clearly going down.
On middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and on off. Bavuma defends it solidly.
Darted on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Very full and on middle. Bavuma drives it to the right of mid on for a single.
Slides a full ball, on middle. Rickelton bunts it through square leg for a single.
Four singles in a row! Flighted and on middle. Bavuma works it to square leg for one more.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
This one spins away but was on the fuller side. Rickelton leans and blocks it out.
Fuller and on off, driven to mid off.
Tad short and on off. Bavuma backs away and punches but straight to short cover.
Full and on middle. Bavuma defends with a straight bat.
Tossed up, on off. Bavuma drops it to the left of covers for a single.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Outside off. Left alone.
Much better! Near the off stump. Rickelton rocks back and keeps it out.
Tosses this up, on off. Rickelton pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Really beautiful shot! Fuller and flighted in the air, around off. Rickelton comes down the track and lofts it to long off for a one-bounce four.
Touch short and outside off. Rickelton punches it through covers for a single.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Rickelton flicks it wide of square leg for a single. Quick single there, good running.
Around off, pushed through covers for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! The decision to bowl with the old ball has done the trick! This is full and angling around off. Rickelton gets on the knee and looks to reverse sweep and the ball takes the gloves and lobs to Yasir Ali at first slip. An appeal for a catch but the umpire is unmoved. Bangladesh were confident as they take it upstairs. The replay shows there was a glove on it and that will be the end of Ryan Rickelton.
Howout: c Yasir Ali b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Verreynne skips down and square drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out.
A flighted ball, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Full and on middle. Bavuma drives it straight. The mid on fielder dives across but slides over the ball and a single is stolen.
Length and on middle. Verreynne on his toes, tucks it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Verreynne shoulders arms to it.
Wow! A first shot of the second new ball and it shows some movement. A length ball, outside off and it nips back in very late. Bavuma lets it through and that whizzed past the off stump.
Tossed up, on off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and around off, Verreynne punches it to covers, on the back foot.
A length ball, around off. Verreynne prods to defend but gets a thick outside edge to short third man where a slight misfield happens but no run is taken.
Tossed up, on off, pushed to covers.
Slightly short and outside off. Verreynne keeps it out.
Angles a full ball, on middle. Verreynne leans and pushes it to covers.
Beaten! Tad shorter, outside off, shaping away a tad. Temba Bavuma hangs back and looks to block this but he misses.
Touch full, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it towards cover.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Khaled Ahmed strikes with the new ball and he gets rid of a set batter now. South Africa lose half their side as Temba Bavuma walks back after a fine knock. A shorter ball, shaping away a tad, outside off. Temba Bavuma hangs back and looks to defend this but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Liton Das dives across to catch the ball, but he fails to get there, and Najmul Hossain Shanto at first slip takes a nice low catch. The third umpire checks if it is a fair catch, and the replay confirms that it is indeed a fair catch and Temba Bavuma has to walk back!
Howout: c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Fuller ball, around middle. Wiaan Mulder flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tad shorter, outside off. Wiaan Mulder pushes it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder stays back and taps it towards point once again. End of a successful over by Khaled Ahmed!
Shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it towards cover.
Fuller now, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans and drives it through cover for a single.
Tosses it up, very full, around middle. Wiaan Mulder pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball, spinning in, around middle. Wiaan Mulder taps it towards square leg.
Fuller length delivery, on the pads. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and defends it out.
Loopy delivery, slower through the air, very full again, around middle. Wiaan Mulder pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, around middle and off, at 136 clicks. Kyle Verreynne leans and blocks it out.
Fullish delivery, around middle, at 132 clicks. Kyle Verreynne taps it towards cover.
Tad shorter, outside off, shaping away a tad. Kyle Verreynne manages to dab it towards the fielder at gully.

A huge shout for LBW, but not given! This one was on a length, nipping back in, on the thigh pads. Kyle Verreynne hops and looks to block this but he misses and gets rapped on the thigh pad. That was probably too high!
Good-length delivery, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.

FOUR! Nicely done! Could have been stopped though! A shorter ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it gently towards deep square leg. Ebadot Hossain runs to his left, but he slips while running and fails to stop the ball. Boundary!
Fuller ball, around middle. Wiaan Mulder defends it back to the bowler.
Swing and a miss! Shorter ball, shaping away, width on offer. Wiaan Mulder looks to cut this away but he misses.
Tailing back in around middle, on a length. Wiaan Mulder defends it out.
Length delivery, around off. Wiaan Mulder blocks it out towards point.
Ebadot Hossain drops it short now, down the leg side. Wiaan Mulder looks to pull but he misses.
On a length, outside off, jagging back in. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone. A maiden over from Ebadot Hossain!
Fuller length delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it back to the bowler.
Angling in, around middle, on a length. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out towards mid-wicket.
Pitches it up, outside off. Kyle Verreynne presses forward and drives it past cover-point for a brace.
Fuller ball, angling in, around middle, at 133 clicks. Kyle Verreynne presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Beaten! Well bowled! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and looks to have a poke at it but he misses.
On a length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Back of a length, angling in, around middle. Wiaan Mulder blocks it out.
Beaten! On a length, outside off, swinging away. Wiaan Mulder leans to block this but he misses and the ball zips past his outside edge.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets that go through to the keeper.
Beaten again! This is good bowling from Ebadot Hossain! On a length again, outside off, shaping away a tad. Wiaan Mulder leans to defend this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Wiaan Mulder taps it towards point.
Tailing back in outside off, on a length. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Khaled Ahmed begins with a length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, nipping away outside off, at 131 clicks. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend this but he decides against it at the end.
This one comes back in around middle, on a length. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
Marginally short, outside off, at 134 clicks. Kyle Verreynne taps it towards point off the back foot.
Length, shaping away outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.

A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! On a length, nipping back in, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick this, but he misses and he gets rapped on his front pad. Khaled Ahmed thinks it's out and Bangladesh opts for a review. No bat involved there, confirms UltraEdge. Ball Tracking indicates it was missing wickets and the impact was also the umpire's call. The on-field decision stands.
Fuller ball, around middle. Wiaan Mulder blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Wiaan Mulder punches it past cover-point for three runs. He gets off the mark after 21 deliveries and with that, we are underway on Day 2.
Beaten! Well bowled! On a length, shaping away a tad outside off. Kyle Verreynne looks to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets that go through to the keeper.
Swinging away, outside off on a length. Kyle Verreynne offers no shot.
Angling in around middle and leg, on a fuller length. Wiaan Mulder works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! First boundary of the day! Shortish delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne rocks back and slashes it past point for boundary.
Fuller delivery this time, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lunges and blocks it out solidly.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Pitches it up again, outside off, at 134 clicks. Kyle Verreynne presses forward and looks to push this on the off side, but he manages to get an outside edge away from the fielder at gully towards third man for a boundary.
On a length, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
Very full on this occasion, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lunges forward and drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
Touch fuller, nipping in, around off. Wiaan Mulder leans and taps it towards point.
Good-length delivery, swinging in around middle, at 137 clicks. Wiaan Mulder dabs it to mid-wicket.
Length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder does not fiddle with that.

EDGED AND FOUR! That was just away from the second slip fielder! A fuller ball, outside off, shaping away. Wiaan Mulder leans to block, this, but the ball goes off the outside edge just away from the diving second slip fielder towards third man for a boundary. Had there been a third slip, that could have been a catch!
Back of a length, around middle. Wiaan Mulder pulls it towards mid-wicket.
On a length, tailing back in outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Pitches it up, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Beaten! Lovely delivery! On a length, around the fourth stump line. Kyle Verreynne stays in his crease and tries to defend this, but he gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball nips away a tad.
Angling in around middle and leg, on a length. Kyle Verreynne defends it out towards the leg side.
Fuller delivery, around middle. Kyle Verreynne pushes it back to the bowler.

Oh dear! Some aggression shown by Khaled Ahmed! On a length now, outside off. Kyle Verreynne taps it back to the bowler with the inner half of his bat. Khaled Ahmed collects the ball and throws it towards the stumps at the striker's end, and the ball goes on to hit Kyle Verreynne's on the glove. A little bit of chatter around. Kyle Verreynne is not happy there!
On a length nipping back in, around middle. Kyle Verreynne taps it towards the leg side.
Fuller ball, shaping away, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off, swinging away. Wiaan Mulder shoulders his arms at it.
Touch fuller again, outside off. Wiaan Mulder does not fiddle with it.
Angling in around middle and leg, on a length. Wiaan Mulder flicks it towards square leg for a brace. It went off the pads so it is given as leg byes.
Tad fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lunges forward and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, shaping away outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets that go through to the keeper.
An inswinger, fuller in length, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it towards mid off.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Short and wide of off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and punches it past cover-point for cracking boundary. 300 up for South Africa!
On a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Bangladesh have their first breakthrough of the day! A beauty by Khaled Ahmed and Kyle Verreynne departs. On a length, nipping back in, around middle. Kyle Verreynne looks to have a push at it but he misses. The ball sneaks in the gap between bat and pad and goes on to hit the top of middle. Khaled Ahmed gets his third wicket and South Africa lose their sixth.
Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Fuller ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj leans and defends it out.
Tad fuller again, around off. Keshav Maharaj lunges and blocks it out solidly. End of a successful over from Khaled Ahmed!
FOUR! Classy! Pitches it, outside off. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and creams his drive past cover for a glorious boundary.
Outside off, on a length. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Length again, outside off. Wiaan Mulder dabs it towards gully and takes a single.
A tight leave by Keshav Maharaj! On a length, nipping back in around the fourth stump line. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.
Yorker-length delivery, width on offer. Keshav Maharaj leans to drive, but he misses.
On a length, around middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj works it away towards square leg for a single. He retains the strike.

Close! On a length, nipping back in, around middle. Keshav Maharaj looks to defend this but he gets an inside edge back onto the pads. The ball then rolls towards the stumps, Keshav Maharaj gets his bat down on time and stops the ball.
FOUR! A gift to Keshav Maharaj! Shorter ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj hops and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Length ball, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj looks to drive this but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads and then rolls towards point. Single taken!
Nipping back in, around middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder flicks it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Keshav Maharaj is jumping on all the bad deliveries! An overpitched delivery, outside off. Keshav Maharaj leans and drives it past cover for a beautiful boundary.
Shorter this time, outside off. Keshav Maharaj stands tall and punches it past cover for a brace.
Length delivery, outside off, tailing back in. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Angling in around the pads. Wiaan Mulder tucks it towards square leg. He wanted a single there, but Keshav Maharaj sends him back.
Down leg, on a length. Wiaan Mulder tickles it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Beaten! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease and looks to defend this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length delivery, swinging in, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj dabs it towards point with soft hands and takes a quick single. He retains the strike!
SIX! A loose delivery and Maharaj attacks it. Shorter and on middle. Maharaj clears his front leg and pummels it over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Slightly short and around off. Maharaj punches it to covers.
FOUR! This time he finds the gap! Shorter and around off. Maharaj punches off the back foot and through covers for a boundary.
Angles a full ball, on middle, spinning away. Blocked out.
Slower this time and turning away. Maharaj waits and taps it late past first slip for a couple.
An arm ball, around off. Maharaj defends on the back foot.
Fuller and outside off. Mulder leans and works it to covers.
Fuller and angling on the pads, whipped to deep square leg for a single.
Outside off. Left alone.
An in-angler around off, Maharaj defends it on the off side.
This is full and outside off. Maharaj thinks to push but withdraws his bat on time.
Now he goes for the drive but again he misses this full ball.
Flatter and on off, pushed to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up, on middle, spins away. Maharaj keeps it out.
Tad short and angling down. Keshav whacks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Full and on odd. Maharaj prods to defend.
SIX! Maharaj is playing with some intent! This is full and around off. Maharaj hammers it straight down the ground, all the way for a biggie. Second six already for him.
A slider, around middle. Maharaj blocks it out.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg.
Length and on off. Mulder punches a bit late and to covers.
Outside off, pushed nicely but finds cover.
BEATEN! Goes wide of the crease and angles a length ball, around the 4th stump channel. Mulder leans to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. This was really close.
Short in length and outside off, it is hit to deep cover for a couple of runs.
Around off. Kept out.
Too full and on leg. Maharaj pushes it across to covers.
A loopy ball, on off. Maharaj knocks it to deep cover for a single.
Slower, flighted and outside off. Mulder drops it to point.
Tossed up, on a length and this one stays low. Mulder gets his bat down to keep it out.
On middle. Blocked out.
Quicker, fuller and on off. Mulder gets on the back foot to defend it.
Fuller and on off. Maharaj lunges and keeps it out on the off side.
This time Maharaj hurries to defend it as he keeps this length ball out.
Around middle and leg, tucked behind square on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, around off. Mulder defends under his eyes.
Touch fuller and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Full, slower at 111 kph, and outside off. Mulder has all the time to muscle this through covers for a boundary. 350 up as well! Also, that brings up the 50-run partnership between these two!
Very full and angling on middle, pushed through the diving cover fielder for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Mulder presses forward and defends it out.
Floated and on middle. Blocked out.
This one keeps on coming with the angle, on leg and Mulder cannot get it past mid-wicket.
Around off, pushed to mid off.
Flighted and on middle. Mulder defends on the front foot.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Maharaj gives a bit of room and punches it past point for a boundary.
Flatter and on off. Maharaj steers it to third man for a single.
SIX! Mulder is having a go now! Tossed up, full and on middle. Mulder skips down and tonks it well over long on where a fielder is there but he is standing up. A biggie.
On middle, worked away to mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and on middle. Maharaj keeps it out.
A slider and on middle. Maharaj dead bats it on the leg side.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
Full again, Mulder waits a bit more and hits it wide of covers to long off for a single.
A loopy ball, on midde. Maharaj lunges and blocks it.
Too full and on off, Maharaj hammers it to silly mid off.
Short and outside off, cut away to deep cover for a single.
Full and on off. Mulder slices his defense to point.
Spinning onto the pads, Maharaj tickles it to long leg and comes back for the second run.
Around off, tapped to covers.
Slower through the air, length and on off. Maharaj punches it to point for a single.
On middle. Blocked to mid-wicket.
Floated and on middle. Mulder comes down the track and looks to defend but misses. It goes off the pads and lobs to square leg. There were cries of catch but there was no bat on it.
Length and on off. Mulder guides it to third man for a single.
Slower through the air, very full, around middle. Wiaan Mulder knocks it past mid off for a single.
Tosses it up, full in length and on middle. Keshav Maharaj leans and blocks it out.
Fuller again, loopy delivery, spinning away. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease and looks to cut this away but he misses.
Shorter ball, spinning away around middle. Keshav Maharaj taps it towards point and rotates the strike.
Loopy delivery, around middle, fuller ball. Wiaan Mulder lunges and defends it out.
Flighted delivery, around middle. Wiaan Mulder has blocked this off the front foot.
Shorter ball, turning in, around middle. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg.
Spinning in, around middle, shorter ball. Keshav Maharaj blocks it out off the back foot.

SIX! BANG! Keshav Maharaj brings up his fifty in style! A slower ball, tosses it up, outside off, fuller ball. Keshav Maharaj strides forward and heaves it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie! That is his 4th fifty in Test cricket!
Fuller delivery, darting it on the pads. Keshav Maharaj steps down and works it away towards mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, spinning in, around middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj flicks it through square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery, full, around the pads. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and taps it towards square leg.

NOT OUT! A mix-up...but Keshav Maharaj survives! A length delivery, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj taps it towards point and leaves his crease for a run. Wiaan Mulder also leaves his crease for a single, but he sends Keshav Maharaj mid-way. Mehidy Hasan quickly runs forwards, collects the ball, and scores a direct-hit at the striker's end. But Keshav Maharaj does well to dive in and makes his ground. The replay shows that Keshav Maharaj was inside the crease on time!
Shorter ball, around middle. Keshav Maharaj looks to pull this but he misses.
On a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj taps it towards cover.
Another bouncer, down leg. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.
A fuller ball, just outside off. Keshav Maharaj looks to drive this but he gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder blocks it towards the leg side.
Flatter and on off, punched to covers for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Beautifully bowled! A loopy delivery, sliding around middle on a fuller length and spinning away sharply. Mulder leans to defend inside the line but gets beaten and the ball rattles the stumps. Taijul Islam gets his fourth wicket of the match.
Howout: b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Full ball, on off. Harmer pushes it to covers.
A slider and goes with the angle, on the pads, flicked to square leg for a single.
No ball! Tossed up, on off, driven nicely but straight to the fielder at covers.
Outside off, turning away. Maharaj leans to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Flatter and around off, turning away. Maharaj tries to play with an angled bat but misses. The keeper whips the bails off and there is a shout for a stumping. Maharaj had his back foot just in air but grounded while the bails were dislodged.
A length ball, on off. Harmer blocks it out.
Short in length and on off. Harmer drops it to point.
Short again, outside off. Harmer steers it to backward point for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length and on middle. Simon defends it out solidly.
Length ball, down the leg side. Harmer misses his flick. No harm done and that will be Lunch on Day 2.
Fuller and angling on middle. Maharaj gets low and blocks it.
Touch short and on off. Maharaj punches hard and to covers for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Harmer prods and works it to covers.
Floated and around off. Harmer goes back in his crease and blocks it.
A loopy ball, on middle. Defended out.
An arm ball, straight on middle. Blocked out on the front foot.
On the pads, tucked to square leg. Harmer wanted a single, actually, it was Maharaj's call and they deny in the end.
A length ball, outside off, it nips away. Maharaj plays inside the line and misses it.
Length and on middle. Maharaj dead bats it.
Outside off. Maharaj has nothing to do with it.
A length ball, around off. Maharaj looks to defend but it goes off the splice to point for a single.
This one jags back in very late. Harmer has his stumps covered as he shoulders arms to it.
Tossed up, on off. Defended towards cover.
On middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off, pushed to long off for a single.
A loopy ball, on middle. Harmer defends it on the deck.
FOUR! Not letting spinner settle in! Full and on middle. Harmer dances down and heaves it to mid-wicket for a boundary.
Around off. Simon guides it to point.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Should've been taken! Late reaction from Yasir Ali! Short of a length, outside off. Maharaj punches with hard hands and it takes the outside edge to first slip. Yasir Ali there, dives to his left but fumbles to hold onto it, touches the finger-tips and races away to the fence.
FOUR! Perfect shot! Fuller and outside off. Maharaj gets low and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Bangs a bounce, around off. Maharaj lets it through to the keeper.
Short in length and on middle. Maharaj hooks it to square leg for a single. 400 up for South Africa, they are cruising through.
On the hips, nudged through mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length and angling down. Maharaj pulls it nicely but straight to square leg.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Harmer keeps it out
On middle. Blocked out.
Angles a full ball, on middle. Maharaj hangs back and defends it.
On the pads, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated and on middle. Harmer defends it solidly on the surface.
FOUR! Top shot! Shorter ball from 'round the wicket, around middle. Keshav Maharaj swivels and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Another short delivery, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.

FOUR! WOW! What a wonderful shot by Keshav Maharaj! On a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj clears his front foot and punches it past cover for a boundary. He expected that to be a short delivery and wanted to pull this.
Back of a length, outside off, Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Very full this time, outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes it towards point. Single taken!
Good-length delivery, angling in, outside off. Simon Harmer leaves it alone.
Shorter ball, around middle. Keshav Maharaj tucks it towards square leg.
Spinning away, around middle and off, shorter ball. Keshav Maharaj pushes it towards cover.
Back of a length, around middle and off, turning away. Keshav Maharaj punches it to cover again.
Shortish delivery, around middle, stays low this one. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Keshav Maharaj presses forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Keshav Maharaj steps down the pitch and looks to slash this away, but the misses.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Another shorter ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease, opens the face of the bat, and guides it past gully towards third man for a boundary. He moves on to the 80s now!
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Another swing and a miss! Tad shorter, outside off. Keshav Maharaj tries to slash this away, but he misses.
Back of a length, around middle. Keshav Maharaj miscues his pull shot towards deep mid-wicket. The ball will not go all the way, but the batters pick up three runs.
Pitches it up, outside off. Simon Harmer defends it out.
Loopy delivery, full, around middle. Keshav Maharaj blocks it out.
Slower through the air, pitches it up, around middle. Keshav Maharaj leans and defends it out.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! No century for Keshav Maharaj! But a five-wicket haul for Taijul Islam! A fuller delivery, around middle, a straighter one. Keshav Maharaj gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this, but he misses it completely. The ball goes on and hits the stumps. A fine knock comes to an end! He recieves a standing ovation as he walks back.
Howout: b Taijul Islam

Commentary: A huge shout for LBW but not given! A fuller ball, turning in, around the pads. Lizaad Williams leans to block this but he misses and gets rapped on the front pad. That was sliding down leg.
Shortish delivery, around middle. Lizaad Williams defends it out.
Fuller ball, around middle. Lizaad Williams defends it out. A wicket-maiden for Lizaad Williams!
Leg bye! Shorter ball, spinning in, around the pads. Simon Harmer misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pads and goes towards fine leg. Leg bye taken!
Swing and a miss! Outside off, spinning away, fuller ball. Lizaad Williams looks to go over cover but he misses.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Lizaad Williams leans and blocks it out.
Tad slower, outside off, shorter ball. Lizaad Williams taps it towards point.
Loopy delivery, full, spinning away outside off. Lizaad Williams leaves it alone.
Slower through the air, full, around off. Lizaad Williams defends it out.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
This is full and sliding down. Harmer comes down and whips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
In the air but safe! Full and on middle. Williams reverse sweeps and lobs it past point for a couple of runs.
Flatter and on middle. Williams blocks it on the leg side.
Straightens, full and on middle. Kept out.
Floated ball, on middle. Williams goes back and looks to defend but gets an inside edge past leg slip and short leg for a single.
Short and outside off. left alone.
Flatter and from around the wicket, around off. Williams defends it out.
Short ball, way outside off. Williams leaves it alone.
Touch fuller and slanting on off. Williams dead bats it.
Sliding down the leg side, tucked to square leg.
Too full and drifting on midde. Williams gets low and defends it.
Tossed up, around off. Harmer hangs back and blocks it out.

Flatter and sliding on the pads. Harmer flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs. Williams had to hurry for the second as there was a throw at the bowler's end but the replay shows he had his bat inside the crease.
On middle, fuller and blocked out.
Flatter and on off. Harmer makes room and punches it to cover. Not in the gap.
Fuller and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket for a single.

A floated ball, outside off and this one spins back in sharply, around middle. Lizaad Williams prods to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Bangladesh take the review. No bat there and Ball Tracking shows the ball is sliding well down and missing the stumps. Taijul Islam thought so but he got tempted to take it upstairs. Bangladesh have no reviews now.
Full and on middle, spinning away. Harmer misses his flick. There is purchase for the spinners now.
On middle. Harmer leans and blocks.
Tossed up, on off. Harmer gets forward and keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off and spinning in. Harmer reverse sweeps it to deep point for a single.
A loopy ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Another solid block from Lizaad Williams to see out the over.
Tossed up, on middle, swept to square leg for a single.
Full and outside off. Williams steps across and dead bats it.
Goes wide of the crease and angles a full ball, on off. Williams gets low to defend under his eyes and almost bottom edges it back on the stumps.
Flatter and outside off. Williams defends nicely this time.
Tossed up, outside off, turning in. Williams flicks it uppishly but well short of the fielder at mid-wicket.
A loopy ball, outside off. Williams blocks it out.
On a length, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer tucks it towards square leg for a brace. Good running there!
Good-length delivery, outside off. Simon Harmer pushes it towards cover.
Back of a length, around middle. Simon Harmer mistimes his pull shot towards deep mid-wicket. Two taken!
Fuller ball, outside off. Simon Harmer leans forward and defends it out.
Short in length, down leg. Simon Harmer leaves it alone.
Another bouncer, around middle. Simon Harmer pulls it gently towards fine leg for a single. He retains the strike!
Beaten! Tosses it up, full, spinning away, outside off. Simon Harmer looks to block this but he misses.
Fuller again, around middle and off. Simon Harmer steps down and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy delivery, outside off, fuller ball. Lizaad Williams pushes it towards cover for a single.
Pitches it up again, outside off. Simon Harmer drives it to the fielder at cover.
FOUR! Perfectly executed sweep shot! A loopy delivery, full, around middle and off. Simon Harmer gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Well bowled! Slower through the air, full again, outside off, spinning away. Simon Harmer hangs back and looks to cut this away, but he misses.
Shorter ball from 'round the wicket, outside off. Lizaad Williams taps it towards point.
On a length this time, outside off. Lizaad Williams pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Lizaad Williams pushes it to the fielder at point.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Angling in around the pads, on a length. Lizaad Williams flicks it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Length delivery, outside off. Lizaad Williams drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Fuller delivery, wide of off. Lizaad Williams leans to drive this, but the ball goes on a bounce towards second slip off the toe end of the bat.
Fuller delivery, around middle. Simon Harmer sweeps it towards through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller ball, around middle and off. Lizaad Williams gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Slower through the air, around middle, pitches it up. Lizaad Williams dances down the pitch and drags it with the inner half of his bat towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Simon Harmer blocks it out.
Tad shorter, outside off. Simon Harmer pushes it towards cover.
Loopy delivery, around middle, fuller ball. Simon Harmer pushes it towards long off for a single. 450 up for South Africa!
Spinning in around middle and leg, slower through the air, fuller ball. Simon Harmer blocks it out.

Pitches it up, down leg. Simon Harmer sweeps it towards deep square leg. They run the first one hard and come back for the second one. There is a throw at the keeper's end, but Simon Harmer dives to make his ground.
Fuller again, down leg. Simon Harmer looks to reverse-sweep this but he misses.
Another fuller ball, around middle. Simon Harmer flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tosses it up, full, outside off. Lizaad Williams blocks it out.
Another loopy delivery, around middle. Lizaad Williams blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.

OUT! STUMPING! Superb work behind the stumps by Liton Das! A flighted ball, full and around off, spinning away. Harmer looks to defend outside the line but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge. The keeper collects and whips the bails off. It is very hard for the third umpire to make a decision as the back foot was slightly in the air. After numerous replays, the third umpire makes a decision. OUT it is. 6th wicket for Taijul Islam, 150th overall in Test cricket.
Howout: st Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Olivier Blocks it on the off side.
Full and on off. Olivier dead bats it again.
too full and on off. Olivier keeps it out.
Full and on off, pushed to short cover.
tossed up, outside off, turning away. Williams prods to defend but misses.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan finally gets one wicket. An arm ball, sliding from round the wicket on middle. Williams gets low and looks to sweep but misses and gets hit near the front pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Lizaad Williams takes a review for formality as that looked plumb. Ball Tracking shows wickets hitting and that will be the end of South Africa's inning. They are all out on 453. That will be Tea on Day 2!
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Starts with a bouncer on middle. Iqbal sits under it.
A length ball, angling outside off and this one comes back in. Iqbal looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Very full and swinging back on middle. Iqbal drives it past mid on and Maharaj there, gives a chase and does well to save a single. Three runs taken. Bangladesh and Tamim Iqbal are off the mark.
A full ball, outside off, swinging away. Joy has a poke at it but misses.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Lovely bowling from Duanne Olivier! An early breakthrough for South Africa! On a driving-length, outside off and swinging away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to drive but gets an outside edge to first slip where Sarel Erwee takes a comfortable catch.
Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Duanne Olivier

Commentary: Short of a length and angling outside off. Shanto is drawn to defend but pulls out.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Iqbal punches it but straight to the cover fielder.
Touch fuller now, around off. Iqbal leans and blocks it.
Length ball, slanting around off. Iqbal prods and defends it solidly.
FOUR! Superb shot! Fuller and around off. Iqbal drives it firmly through mid off for a boundary.
Good end to the over! On a length and in the channel of uncertainty. Iqbal looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, angling outside off and nips back in sharply. Shanto looks to drive but gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
On the pads, hit to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! Slants a length ball, outside off. Santo square drives it past point for a boundary.
Tad fuller and around the 5th stump channel. Shanto tries to defend across but misses.
Another away-angler outside off. Shanto leaves it.
Length and on off. Shanto keeps it out.
Sightly full and around off. Iqbal works it to point.
FOUR! A full ball, around off. Iqbal looks to drive straight down but this goes off the slice of the bat and through point for a boundary.
Around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Iqbal looking good so far, some exclusive shots! Fuller and outside off. Iqbal leans into his drive and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Around off, fuller and this is defended out.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over and this time the shot is even better! Short of a length, outside off. Iqbal punches off the back foot and through point for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Shanto taps it to point.
FOUR! Easy one! Length ball,  angling on the pads. Shanto tickles it to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, outside off. Shanto chops it to backward point.
Short of a length and on middle, pulled away to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Iqbal looks to cut but mistimes it to mid-wicket.
Outside off. Left alone.
On a length, angling in, around middle and leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto tucks it towards square leg.
